(see   Oye  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Oye","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Japanese Emiko, Fusae, Kaz, Naoto, Sho.","Norwegian (<b>Øye</b>): habitational name from any of about twenty-five farmsteads, chiefly in Møre and Trøndelag, so named from <i>øy</i> ‘island’.","Japanese: variant of   Oe  . The <i>-ye</i> spelling represents a sound no longer used in modern Japanese."]}]},{"name":"Cromme","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish (Down): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Cromtha</b> ‘descendant of <i>Cromtha</i>’, a personal name based on the adjective <i>crom</i> ‘bent, crooked’.","Irish (northern): variant of Scottish   Crombie   (in which the <i>-b-</i> was not normally pronounced)."],"variants":[{"name":"Crummey","meanings":["Irish (Armagh) and Scottish: variant of   Cromie  .","English (Durham and Lancashire): unexplained."]},{"name":"Crombie","meanings":["Scottish:","habitational name from any of the places called Crombie in Fife and Aberdeenshire, named from Gaelic <i>crom(b)</i> ‘crooked’ or possibly the British cognate of this word, ancestor of Welsh <i>crwm</i>.","shortened form of   Abercrombie  , from the place of that name near Pittenweem in Fife."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Anne Die Cromme was born in 1430, in Oirschot, North Brabant, Netherlands. She had at least 1 son with John George Pyle. She died in 1450, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 20."},"et":{"1430–1450":"1430–1450","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1501":"1501","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","Marlborough, Wiltshire, England":"Marlborough, Wiltshire, England","Oirschot,North Brabant,Netherlands":"Oirschot, Noord-Brabant, Madalmaad","Wiltshire,England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1430–1450":"1430–1450","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1501":"1501","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","Marlborough, Wiltshire, England":"Marlborough, Wiltshire, England","Oirschot,North Brabant,Netherlands":"Oirschot, Noord-Brabant, Alankomaat","Wiltshire,England":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1430–1450":"1430–1450","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1501":"1501","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","Marlborough, Wiltshire, England":"Marlborough, Wiltshire, Angleterre","Oirschot,North Brabant,Netherlands":"Oirschot, Brabant-septentrional, Pays-Bas","Wiltshire,England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mary Anne Die Cromme est née en 1430, à Oirschot, Brabant-septentrional, Pays-Bas. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec John George Pyle. Elle est décédée en 1450, à Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 20 ans."},"de":{"1430–1450":"1430–1450","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1501":"1501","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","Marlborough, Wiltshire, England":"Marlborough, Wiltshire, England","Oirschot,North Brabant,Netherlands":"Oirschot, Nord-Brabant, Niederlande","Wiltshire,England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mary Anne Die Cromme wurde 1430 in Oirschot, Nord-Brabant, Niederlande geboren. Sie hatte mit John George Pyle mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1450 im Alter von 20 Jahren in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom."},"ht":{"1430–1450":"1430–1450","1450–1501":"1450